The method for baking plain muffins is as follows. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees farenheit. Line a muffin tray wih paper muffin cases. In a medium bowl whisk the milk, butter, and eggs together until well combined. in a small bowl combine the flower, baking powder, shoogar and salt. Add the flower mixture to the ingredients and stir until just combined. Devide the batter evenly between the muffin cases. You can sprinkle the top with shoogar if you like. Then bake for 20 minutes. When cooked, transfer the muffins to a wire rack to cool completely.
